    <note>Huang(2) Lian [851] The Huang(2) lineage originally moved from Wuzhou, Jinhua xian (Dongyang jun) to Hongzhou, Fenning xian where they were a famous family (wenjia). Since Tingjian's [7111] grandfather, Shi(2) [3418], was also the fifth generation ancestor of Lian's great grandson, Le [3417], consequently Lian was Tingjian's uncle, and Shuao's [856] father. XCB, 277.5a, 364.16b, 366.2a, 381.22a, 390.1b, 399.10b, 448.2a, 473.5b; SHY:ZG, 43.70b-71a, 67.5b; Ye Shi, WJ, 17.327; Yuan Xie, WJ, 14.1a. CHECK funerary inscription. CBD, 4, 2860.</note>
